N:database-schema-design
D:Design or review SQL and NoSQL schemas with clear tradeoffs for entities, relationships, indexes, constraints, and migrations. Use when the user needs a new schema, ERD, migration plan, schema refactor, or database performance guidance.
G:database schema SQL NoSQL PostgreSQL MySQL MongoDB migration ERD indexing normalization
U[5]:
  Design a new relational or document-oriented schema
  Review an existing schema for missing relationships, indexes, or integrity rules
  Choose between normalization and denormalization for a known workload
  Plan migrations, backfills, and rollout order for live systems
  Produce an ERD, table list, document model, or index strategy for review
S[6]{n,action}:
  1,Triage the storage and workload shape
  2,Model entities, relationships, and ownership
  3,Plan integrity and performance together
  4,Stage migrations and rollout deliberately
  5,Produce the deliverable in a reviewable format
  6,Pull support files only when needed
R[3]:
  references/sql-schema-recipes.md
  references/nosql-schema-recipes.md
  references/migration-review-checklist.md
